beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Kind of a cabbage smell thats not to pleasing. Apperance is good. nice earthtones. the beer has a nice bite, and not much in the way of aftertaste. Its not a bad IPA but there are alot better out there

I normaly dont buy a bottle of brew because of the label...but you gotta admit thats a cool looking bottle. Well anyhow the beer inside was very good. strong enough to keep the coors drinkers from buying it, but not so for true ale drinkers. lots of flavors in this one, even a little nutty. Buy it for the label, drink it for the taste

In 1980 I pulled into Cork and being a good little sailor I went strait to the pub. I asked for the local brew and for the first time in my life I had a Guinness. I have never had a beer moment quite like that. It was almost a religous experience. From that day Guinness has always been my favorate tap. My rating here is for Tap Guinness only. canned and bottle would rate slighty lower
I dont know what to tell ya about this one. There were so many things wrong with it. I drank two and the rest of the 6-pak sat in the fridge for weeks. I finnaly dumped them down the sink.
what a yummy Ale. I was not aware of the 7.7 content until I started feeling fuzzy and warm. Nice end of the day beer. I now keep a 6-pak tucked away for guests. good stuff.

I just pick this up off the shelf for a lark. I was so very impressed. The taste is smooth and very enjoyable. I would highy recommened this Porter to anyone wanting to venture into other type of Beers. Go find this one.
